{
  "doc_id": "52119",
  "text": "To overcome some of the limitations in data availability and to recover historical information, scientists have documented changes in marine ecosystems using fishers' perceptions (also called Local Ecological Knowledge, LEK, or Traditional Ecological Knowledge, TEK) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . In the Mediterranean Sea, applications to recover this knowledge have yield interesting results, such as information on depletion of large predators [CITATION_6] and on changes in marine fish diversity due to meridionalization [CITATION_7] .",
